Citigroup’s Banamex Names Torres as CEO of Bank Unit

-- B y   B e n   B a i n   a n d   C a r l o s   M a n u e l   R o d r i g u e z
-- 
2011-12-09T00:22:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-08/citigroup-s-banamex-names-ernesto-torres-as-ceo-of-bank-unit.html
(Corrects to update position of Zorrilla and Quiroz in
second paragraph.)  Ernesto Torres will take over as
chief executive officer of  Citigroup Inc. (C) ’s Banamex banking unit
starting January 1, the bank said in an e-mailed statement.  Torres will replace Enrique Zorrilla, who will assume the
vice presidency of the executive committee. Fernando Quiroz, a
member of the executive committee, announced his retirement,
effective next April, the bank said today.  Javier Arrigunaga will remain chief executive officer of
Grupo Financiero Banamex, according to the statement.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Ben Bain in New York at 
